1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,760
The best time to surface revenue risk is

2
00:00:01,820 --> 00:00:03,540
six weeks before the quarter ends, not

3
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:04,200
six days.

4
00:00:05,070 --> 00:00:06,730
Most teams find out a deal is at risk

5
00:00:06,770 --> 00:00:07,350
when it slips.

6
00:00:07,940 --> 00:00:09,520
The rep updates the close date.

7
00:00:10,330 --> 00:00:11,740
The manager asks what happened.

8
00:00:12,290 --> 00:00:13,870
The answer is usually something that was

9
00:00:13,940 --> 00:00:15,040
visible weeks earlier.

10
00:00:15,570 --> 00:00:17,020
Stakeholder access dropped off.

11
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:19,180
Next steps went unconfirmed.

12
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:21,470
The economic buyer never engaged.

13
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:24,350
AI can surface those signals early when

14
00:00:24,370 --> 00:00:25,870
it is connected to call recordings,

15
00:00:26,290 --> 00:00:28,410
email activity, and CRM data.

16
00:00:29,230 --> 00:00:30,710
The question is whether the team has

17
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:32,340
built the inspection habit to act on

18
00:00:32,430 --> 00:00:34,380
early signals rather than wait for the

19
00:00:34,410 --> 00:00:34,680
slip.

20
00:00:36,130 --> 00:00:37,810
Revenue risk is not a forecasting

21
00:00:37,870 --> 00:00:38,270
problem.

22
00:00:38,670 --> 00:00:40,250
It is an operating rhythm problem.

23
00:00:41,090 --> 00:00:42,900
Teams that use AI to inspect deals

24
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:45,130
weekly, not just at quarter end, build a

25
00:00:45,180 --> 00:00:46,910
different kind of pipeline confidence.

26
00:00:47,790 --> 00:00:50,310
Follow A-Gent for the agent-first GTM

27
00:00:50,370 --> 00:00:50,800
playbook.
